I"Ñ@<h2 id="was-that-click-bait">Was that click bait?</h2>

<p>Why would I write such a potentially combative title for this article?</p>

<p>Well, I think I understand what‚Äôs going on for me there. There‚Äôs a parallel to how I frame my political views.</p>

<p>In that case, I‚Äôve spent most of the last 25 years seeing targets on the foreheads of the politically conservative amongst us. When asked why, I‚Äôd say something along the lines of <em>‚Äúit‚Äôs just so easy when I used to be conservative in my early 20s‚Äù</em></p>

<p>There was an arc of living and learning that led to this thinking, documented in <strong>Green Crash</strong> (write to me for a copy - there are real people referred to who might not appreciate me making this public)</p>

<p>Let me tie together:</p>

<ul>
  <li>my Belief System</li>
  <li><a href="https://www.allenandunwin.com/browse/books/general-books/current-affairs-politics/Growth-Fetish-Clive-Hamilton-9781741140781">Growth Addiction</a></li>
  <li>The themes of <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sapiens:_A_Brief_History_of_Humankind">Sapiens</a></li>
  <li>My take on  <a href="https://www.benburke.org/game-theory-in-two-lines-of-code/">Game Theory</a></li>
  <li>The <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Maximum_power_principle">Maximum Power Principle</a></li>
</ul>

<p>I hope to explain why I‚Äôm no fun to ‚Äòplay against‚Äô and why I always let the <a href="https://www.starwars.com/video/let-the-wookiee-win">Wookie Win</a></p>

